Very good Japanese food here! Esp with 50% off entire menu now, the food here is very worth trying! My 2 most fav dishes here are: Hotate Canape and Soft Shell Crab Karaage.
Great food at reasonable prices. Will definitely go back and lunch there when I visit Ulun Danu temple in future for yummy food+ reasonable price + great view!
Service was very slow. Food tastes below average. Oh btw, its raw prawn salad should have garlic slices to be authentic. Not a good location to visit at night. Won't visit again.

Good Tom yam soup. Taste should be more intense but ingredients just nice. Great Garlic Chilli Kang Kong. Good fish cakes. Yummy Red Rubi. Overall: Great and authentic but more intense flavours pls!:)
Free flow rice and water!! Spiciness level: medium - high... A bit pricey. Mushroom goreng salad is a must try, followed by spicy stir-fried squid. Don't: do not try "The Textures of Coconut" at $9.
Why u should try this: 1)Nett price 2)lovely ambience 3)Thai Prawn Sashimi (raw and super spicy!! But yummy!!) oh but don't expect too much for its tomyam soup. 😉
